{{SupportPage|vendor=D-Link|model=DI-714P%2B|vs_id=19}} "103408600Y1" and "WPA400AM-Y1" is silkscreened on the mainboard. It is possible these units may have differing wireless modules (which do not appear to be standard PCMCIA). This particular one uses a [[National Datacomm NWH1021]]. The FCC photos depict the device with an RFMD based '''DBTel''' card, however, the FCC photos depict a different main board (probably for the A1 revision). The OUI of the MAC on the wireless module label is 00:80:C6 ('''National Datacomm'''). The OUI on the label affixed to the router is 00:0D:88 ('''D-Link''').
The RP-SMA antenna leads on the case exterior are soldered directly to the wireless module. == Images == File:DI-714P+ higherres.jpg|main [[Has images::external| ]] File:D-Link DI-714P+ rev B1 case board top.jpg|board top, in case File:D-Link DI-714P+ rev B1 board card removed.jpg|board top, removed from case, card removed File:D-Link DI-714P+ rev B1 board bot.jpg|board bottom [[Has images::internal| ]]
